duck: CXP (connector), a connector system with 12 × 10 Gbit/s links suitable for 100 Gbit/s Ethernet, three 40 Gbit/s Ethernet, or 12 × 10 Gbit/s Ethernet. The C is the Roman numeral for 100 as a memory aid.
Carson Airport, an airport in Carson City, Nevada, with the FAA location identifier CXP.
Constellation Program (abbreviated CxP), NASA's newest program of manned space flight.
Xtra Airways, a charter airline with the ICAO airline designator CXP.
Tunggul Wulung Airport, an airport in Central Java with the IATA airport code CXP.
Mavic CXP Rims, a brand of bicycle rims.
